   "body" : "mapAlreadyAskedFor does not keep track of which peer has a request queued for a particular tx. As a result, a peer can blind a node to a tx indefinitely by sending many invs for the same tx, and then never replying to getdatas for it. Each inv received will be placed 2 minutes farther back in mapAlreadyAskedFor, so a short message containing 10 invs would render that tx unavailable for 20 minutes.\r\n\r\nThis is fixed by disallowing a peer from having more than one entry for a particular inv in mapAlreadyAskedFor at a time.",
